        },
        "text": "In line with the Commission's stated objective to simplify and ensure a level playing field for businesses, and to reduce legal uncertainty, CER would advocate that the DFA should clearly exempt these standard, beneficial, and transparent practices. Regulating them would not address the problem definition of \"Lack of digital fairness for consumers\" or \"Unclear rules for businesses and market fragmentation\" but instead would limit consumer benefits.",
